<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910410-0013</DOCNO><DOCID>910410-0013.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Prudential Insurance Co.:   Concern Restructures Group,   Plans to Trim Staff by 70</HL><DATE>04/10/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>FULL LINE INSURANCE (INF)INSURANCE (INS)</IN><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)</RE><LP>   Prudential Insurance Co. of America said that it isrestructuring its private placement group and plans to trimits roughly 500 member staff in the unit by 60 to 70positions.   The reorganization will divide the unit into two groups,one that will handle leveraged buy-outs and one forasset-backed securities. Previously, the unit's activitieswere divided on a regional basis. As part of the reshuffling,five of the company's regional offices will be combined withother locations, leaving six regional offices.</LP><TEXT>   All of the employees in the regional offices are beingoffered voluntary separation packages. All employeescompanywide with more than five years experience are beingoffered the package as well. A spokesman said the companyexpects 60 to 70 people to accept the offer.   A spokesman said the private placement group's businessslowed last year to $8.3 billion from $10.6 billion in 1989.</TEXT></DOC>